# Tribal Legendary Hunt localization

# Hunt started - legendary creature spawned
tribal-hunt-popup-legendary-started = A legendary beast has been sighted! The tribe must hunt it down and claim its legendary hide for armor crafting.

# Location indicator - periodically broadcast
tribal-hunt-popup-creature-location = The legendary beast was last seen at {$location}. Move swiftly!

# Creature health indicator
tribal-hunt-popup-creature-health = The legendary beast is wounded ({$health}% health remaining).

# Successful hunt completion
tribal-hunt-popup-legendary-complete = The legendary beast has been slain! Legendary leather has been claimed. The tribe is energized with speed blessing for {$seconds} seconds!

# Creature escaped/timed out
tribal-hunt-popup-legendary-escaped = The legendary beast escaped into the wastes. The hunt has failed.

# Player too far from hunt
tribal-hunt-popup-creature-too-far = You are too far from the hunt grounds to participate.

# Creature sighted notification
tribal-hunt-popup-creature-sighted = A legendary beast has been sighted nearby!

# Skinning/harvesting indicator
tribal-hunt-popup-skinning = The legendary hide is being harvested...

# Harvest complete
tribal-hunt-popup-hide-harvested = Legendary leather obtained from the slain beast!
